# Session Knowledge Capture Protocol

At the end of any session where you performed **troubleshooting, API exploration, or script development** in this VCF lab environment, you MUST offer to update the relevant knowledge base files before ending. This ensures that every new discovery is captured for future sessions.

## When to Trigger

Trigger this protocol when ALL of the following are true:
- The session involved **diagnosing or resolving** a VCF-related issue, OR exploring a new API/pattern
- You discovered something **not already documented** in the existing skill files
- The user has not explicitly declined knowledge capture

## What to Update

Review your session for any of the following new learnings:

| Learning Type | Target File |
| --- | --- |
| New API endpoint, auth flow, or credential | `.cursor/skills/vcf-9-api/SKILL.md` |
| New failure pattern, root cause, or fix | `.cursor/skills/vcf-troubleshooting/SKILL.md` |
| New pitfall, version difference, or gotcha | Both skills (Pitfalls section + relevant troubleshooting section) |
| New environment detail (IPs, hostnames, paths) | `.cursor/skills/vcf-9-api/SKILL.md` (Architecture section) |
| Certificate ops (proxy, Vault PKI, PKCS#7, SDDC cert workflow) | `.cursor/skills/vcf-certs/SKILL.md` |
| Anything related to the holorouter | `.cursor/skills/holorouter/SKILL.md` |

## How to Update

1. **Check existing content first** — read the target skill file to avoid duplicating what's already documented
2. **Add new issues** to the Table of Known Issues (troubleshooting) or Critical Pitfalls (API)
3. **Add detailed sections** with Symptom, Diagnosis, Root Cause, and Fix subsections
4. **Update the skill description** in the YAML frontmatter if new keywords are needed for skill matching
5. **Keep the `.mdc` rule lean** — only add quick-reference reminders there, not detailed procedures

## Format Standards

- Troubleshooting sections follow the pattern: `## N. Title` with `**Symptom**`, `**Diagnosis**` (with code block), `**Root Cause**`, `**Fix**` (with code block)
- API sections follow the pattern: `## N. Title` with code blocks showing curl/python examples
- Pitfalls are one-line entries: `N. **Bold summary**: Detail explanation.`
- NEVER store passwords. Instead, provide details on how or where to obtain them
